# DATA MODEL — Grain v6

The database is action-based.

Logging is event-driven.

---

## journeys

Represents a long-term declared direction.

Fields:
- id (uuid)
- user_id (uuid)
- title (string, max 60)
- why (string, max 200)
- category_id (uuid, nullable)
- weekly_commitment (numeric: 0.5–20 in 0.5 increments)
- role (primary | secondary)
- status (active | paused | archived)
- created_at
- paused_at (nullable)
- archived_at (nullable)

Constraints:
- Max 3 active journeys per user.
- Only one primary journey per user.
- Paused journeys excluded from integrity rate.

---

## journey_categories

Static reference table for onboarding filtering.

Fields:
- id
- key
- name

---

## actions

User-owned reusable actions.

Fields:
- id
- user_id
- category_id (nullable)
- title (max 80)
- is_active
- created_at

Actions can be reused across journeys.

---

## journey_actions

Many-to-many join between journeys and actions.

Fields:
- id
- user_id
- journey_id
- action_id
- source (suggested | custom)
- sort_order
- created_at

Constraint:
- unique (journey_id, action_id)

---

## action_logs

Event-based logging.

Each row = one action session.

Fields:
- id
- user_id
- journey_id
- action_id
- log_date (date)
- duration (0.5 | 1.0 | 1.5 | 2.0 | 3.0)
- note (optional, max 140)
- logged_at

Rules:
- Multiple logs per day allowed.
- Same action can be logged multiple times per day.
- No unique constraint on date.
- Unlogged days have no rows.

---

## weekly_summaries (computed)

Fields:
- week_start
- journey_id
- commitment
- actual
- delta
- zero_log_days
- needle_moved (boolean)
- recalibrated (boolean)

actual = SUM(action_logs.duration) grouped by week.

---

## Enforcement

action_logs inserts must only succeed if:

- action.user_id = auth.uid()
- journey.user_id = auth.uid()
- journey_actions contains matching journey_id + action_id + user_id

Never bypass RLS.